	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102082934172312><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=3614&mid=102082934172312>Erud's Crossing</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=3614&mid=102082934172312#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=84722><span id=Scholar>ktadema</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>53 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, May 7th 11:50 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Erud's Crossing has the most wisps/square foot easily in EQ.&nbsp;&nbsp;This has become my favorite hunting ground for finding Burned Out Lightstones, which are used for Journeyman's Research practice runes (B).  There always seems to be one wisp around on that little island, and when you first get to the island, before you've had time to weed them out, there are usually about four of them.  They spawn back pretty quickly too, so there is not much waiting around before you see another.  Also a great place for LS and GLS if that's what you are after.<br>&nbsp;<br><br>***Givins, Erudite Wizard, Rodcet Nife***<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
