<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=103254628958780></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103254628958780><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=3614&mid=103254628958780>RE: Erud's Crossing</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=3614&mid=103254628958780#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=168757><span id= >Brunansky</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>36 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 20th 2:40 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree about Erud's Crossing. I went there to collect these for spell research. In about 2 hours, I collected about 35 burned out lightstones. I also kept selling the regular and the greater lightstones as I collected them. I easily made over 50pp in this 2 hours just from those. Look for the rock/statue with the ogre standing next to it. This seemed to be the most common spawn point, but they do spawn elsewhere. The spawn time is quick. You can usually find 5-6 wisps every 10 minutes, and every one has one of the 3 variations of lightstone. The regular lightstone sell for just under 1pp and the greater stones sell for over 4pp.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
